  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Statement.}\n\nSimplicial-complex entropy is derived from the distribution of simplex counts or Betti-sector contributions across dimensions of the complex.\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\n\nLet \\(K\\) be a finite simplicial complex and let \\(f_k\\) denote the number of \\(k\\)-simplices in \\(K\\). The total simplex mass is\n\\[\nF_K=\\sum_{k\\ge 0} f_k.\n\\]\nWhen \\(F_K>0\\), define the dimension distribution\n\\[\nq_k=\\frac{f_k}{F_K},\\qquad \\sum_{k\\ge 0}q_k=1.\n\\]\nThe simplicial entropy is\n\\[\nS_{\\Delta}(K)=-\\sum_{k\\ge 0}q_k\\log q_k.\n\\]\nThe same complex carries the Euler characteristic\n\\[\n\\chi(K)=\\sum_{k\\ge 0}(-1)^k\\beta_k,\n\\]\nwhere \\(\\beta_k=\\operatorname{rank}H_k(K)\\) is the \\(k\\)th Betti number. A topology-weighted entropy diagnostic is then\n\\[\n\\mathcal{E}_{K}=S_{\\Delta}(K)+\\lambda\\,|\\chi(K)|.\n\\]\n\n\\paragraph{Wolfram Form.}\n\\begin{verbatim}\nq = f/Total[f];\nSDelta = -Total[q*Log[q]];\nChiK = Sum[(-1)^k*beta[k], {k, 0, kmax}];\nEK = SDelta + lambda*Abs[ChiK];\n\\end{verbatim}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\n\nID 0227 converts the combinatorial body of a simplicial complex into an entropy measure while keeping the Euler-characteristic aggregate visible as the topological closure term.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
